[The news reports above report the death of an elderly woman with listeriosis after hospitalization in late January 2019 for an unrelated condition. Listeriosis in this patient has been linked to the commercial food caterer "I Cook Foods" in the town of Dandenong South (Australia), which supplies prepared food to multiple hospitals and other institutions caring for the elderly and "meals on wheels" in the Melbourne area.

The "I Cook Foods" website says that it produces foods that have its texture modified to varying degrees (soft, minced, pureed), although its appearance is made to conform to its original form, e.g., "broccoli looks like a floret of broccoli, carrots look like carrot batons and roast potatoes look like slices of roast potatoes," to enhance visual appeal for people with dysphagia (https://www.icookfoods.com.au/texture-modified-foods).

Ready-to-eat products that do not require further cooking before eating, such as smoked salmon or cold-cut meats (e.g., ham), are recognized as potential sources for listeriosis. Unpasteurized milk and cheese and other milk products made from unpasteurized milk are other frequent sources of listeriosis. However, the source in some outbreaks has been food contaminated with _Listeria_ only after cooking or pasteurization.

In all, 6 positive samples of _Listeria_ were found at the company's Dandenong South kitchen during an investigation, but no information is given on types of food that may have been implicated, although all food items produced by "I Cook Foods" have been recalled. Genotyping the environmental isolates and the isolate from the patient will confirm the association, if the genotypes match.

Dandenong South, with a population of 160 residents, is an industrialized suburb of Melbourne, Victoria, Australia, 31 km (19 miles) southeast of Melbourne's central business district. Its local government area is the City of Greater Dandenong (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dandenong_South,_Victoria). A map showing the location of Dandenong South can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Dandenong+South+VIC+3175,+Australia. - Mod.ML

